QUERY: most common cancer millennial
DATE: 12-03-2024
According to research, the most common cancers for millennials are kidney, pancreatic, and small intestine cancers: [1, 2, 3]
Risk
The risk of these cancers is two to three times higher for millennials than for baby boomers. [3]
Incidence
The incidence rate for these cancers has increased with each successive birth cohort since around 1920. [2]

Other cancers that are more common in millennials include:
Liver cancer in women
Bile duct cancer in women
Uterine corpus cancer
Colorectal cancer
Non-cardia gastric cancer
Gallbladder cancer
Ovarian cancer
Testicular cancer
Anal cancer in men
Kaposi sarcoma in men [2, 3, 4, 5]
The number of young Americans diagnosed with cancer has increased by 80% over the last 30 years. However, for most cancers, the risk of dying from the disease has stabilized or declined among younger people. [3, 4]

The environmental health field is working to identify which chemicals may be driving the increase in colorectal cancer. [6]


